Okay yes, I'm noob -whatever - that being said. I'm not computer illiterate.. just new to torrents and dvd burning. 

Programs I'm using: 
ConvertXDvd
Nero 7
Magic ISO
Winrar

Recurring problem:
[Some] torrents I download are in winrar. I do have winrar. When i d/l the file I get several files.. usually around 25 of them are winrar files.. the others aren't identified by my computer. The extentions are .r31, .r32, etc. I keep trying to extract here the 25 files identified by winrar.. which gives me one .img file. Nero and Magic ISO keep burning up to chapter 11 and saying burning complete. I've now gone through about 7 blank DVD's and through trial and error, and error, and error - can't figure out the problem. 

When I get a .avi file.. I simply use ConvertxDVD, convert, then slow my speed to burn and it works.. but I can't use convertxdvd because it's a .img file. Help anyone?

ne0rotic:
img is actual a cd/dvd image can written to cd/dvd. Normally movies torrents with img bin iso files are either DVDs or VCDs images. So can burn them... I would suggest u to install PowerISO so u can varify img before burning it

and about the rar files. just open .rar with winrar and extract it. winrar will automatically load r31 r32... when needed.

hope that help. take care
